<item>
            <title>[MATH-584] KMeansPlusPlusClusterer incorrectly selects initial cluster centers and is unnecessarily slow</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-584</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The chooseInitialClusters() method declares sum as an int, when it should be double.  It also is quite slow because it contains a lot of unnecessary computation.  I&apos;ll attached a patch which corrects the problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found the problems while comparing an optimized implementation of KMeans++ I&apos;ve been working on with the one in commons math. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
